INSERT INTO `field_data_field_bio` VALUES ('node','member',0,8,8,'und',0,'Thomas is a proud father of three girls (3G) and was inspired by his 3Gs to establish CoderDojo NOVA.  He got into coding in his college years at Virginia Tech (B.A. Economics and M.S. Applied Economics); and is very passionate about Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math (STEM) and its impact on the future of our kids.  He currently works at the U.S. Department of State.',NULL),('node','member',0,16,16,'und',0,'David has been interested in programming and computers since he started writing code at age 6, and wishes there was something like CoderDojo around when he was a kid. He is a graduate of University of Maryland College Park (B.S. Mechanical Engineering) and Virginia Tech (M.S. Systems Engineering) and currently works as a management consultant for ReefPoint Group.',NULL),('node','member',0,17,17,'und',0,'Gelila is the proud mother of the 3Gs and co-consipirator/founder of CoderDojo NOVA.  She is a graduate of Virginia Tech in Information Systems and Accounting and currently works at the Executive Office of the President.',NULL),('node','member',0,18,18,'und',0,'Jason is a program assistant at the World Bank Group in Washington DC. He is a member of a team that produces the World Development Report—one of the Bank’s annual flagship reports. Jason has over 14 years of experience in technical and administrative support.',NULL),('node','member',0,19,19,'und',0,'Michelle is a software engineer at Applied Predictive Technologies, a data analytics firm that helps businesses evaluate the impact of their decisions. She learned how to program and how to teach others to program at Dartmouth College, where she received her B.A. in computer science in June 2014.',NULL),('node','member',0,20,20,'und',0,'Anteneh is an IT Consultant with over 12 years of experience in programming.  His interest in programming started at T.C. Williams high school with the introduction to Word Perfect 5.1.  He enjoys coding and solving problems.  He graduated from Virginia Commonwealth University with a B.S. in Computer Information Systems with a concentration in application development.',NULL),('node','member',0,21,21,'und',0,'Patrick is a Database Engineer for i360, a political data provider for non-profits and national campaigns. He graduated with a Computer Science degree from Georgia Tech in 2008, and has been hooked on computer programming ever since he was introduced to it in the 10th grade. His favorite thing about coding is how empowering it can feel to have a computer do something you told it to do. He wants to share that excitement with students (and parents!), to enable them to harness the technology changing the world.',NULL),('node','member',0,22,22,'und',0,'Al is the manager of Mott Clubhouse and leader of the Rockets and Robotics program for the Fairfax County Clubhouses.',NULL),('node','member',0,23,23,'und',0,'A self-described “transit data nerd”, Dag has run the full gamut of data in transportation. Starting as a software engineer and mathematician by schooling, Dag built data collection and NTD reporting solutions for the FTA, Chicago Transit Authority, GDOT, TDOT, and more. Dag subsequently moved into a project management role, advising the development of data collection projects that generated actionable intelligence for transit systems in Alabama, Georgia, Maryland and Virginia. Dag is the CEO of Transit Lab, a data analytics company dedicated to building smarter cities by improving data collection, reporting, analysis and modeling practices and harnessing the power of big data to better inform transit decision-making.',NULL),('node','member',0,24,24,'und',0,'Zerai is an Operations Officer at NDI. He’s passionate about technology and photography. He is a graduate of Addis Ababa University (LL.B.), Universite de Montpellier (DU Legal Information Systems), and George Mason University (M.A. International Commerce and Policy).',NULL),('node','member',0,25,25,'und',0,'Steve was captivated by the hour of code promotional materials and decided to use his coding powers for good. He went to school for way too long and picked up a B.S. from the University of Rochester and an M.S. and a Ph.D. from Duke University all in Mechanical Engineering. He does R&D for the Navy at the Naval Research Lab in DC. Steve wants to share the thrill of solving puzzles and creating something from nothing using the magic of coding.',NULL),('node','member',0,26,26,'und',0,'Ria is passionate about introducing young people to the field of computer science, teaching them how to program, showing them how to create something from nothing, and making them thirsty to learn more. She currently teaches Computer Science at Thomas Jefferson High School for Science and Technology.',NULL),('node','member',0,27,27,'und',0,'Benjamin Parrish is a 10 year United States Army veteran with 6 years of software engineering development in the federal government space. Benjamin is an Army Blackhawk helicopter pilot for the Virginia Army National Guard, and is a former Field Artillery officer. Benjamin deployed to Iraq from 2006-2007 as a platoon leader for A company 2/337th PFAR. Benjamin enjoys programming iOS mobile apps in his free time, and is a full time software engineer for The HumanGeo Group, LLC. Benjamin has advanced experience in front end and back end development for websites with focus on ASP.NET MVC and Java Groovy/Grails back end and HTML5/CSS3/JavaScript front end.',NULL);
