Code to Learn: why programming prepares kids for more than math</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.hackingplay.com/children-learning-to-program-5-misconceptions-most-parents-have/#sthash.n7xDrnRH.dpuf\" target=\"_blank\">Children Learning To Program: 5 Misconceptions Most Parents Have</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://stemconnector.org/\" target=\"_blank\">STEM Connector newsletter</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://lifehacker.com/how-and-why-to-teach-your-kids-to-code-510588878\" target=\"_blank\">How and Why to Teach Your Kids to Code</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://techcrunch.com/2013/09/08/super-fun-kid-time-9-year-old-programmer/\" target=\"_blank\">9 year old creates app ‘Super Fun Kid Time’ at Disrupt Hackathon</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.codecademy.com/blog/71-how-kids-can-learn-to-code\" target=\"_blank\">How Kids Can Learn to Code</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Learning Resources:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://scratch.mit.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">Scratch</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.thehelloworldprogram.com/html-markup-game/\" target=\"_blank\">Super Markup Man</a>&nbsp;– learn html the fun way</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://code.org/\" target=\"_blank\">code.org</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://codeacademy.com/\" target=\"_blank\">codeacademy.com</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.khanacademy.org/\" target=\"_blank\">KhanAcademy.com</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/\" target=\"_blank\">stackoverflow.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scholarship Opportunities:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.girlswhocode.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Girls Who Code</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://ww2.ncwit.org/award/award.index.php\" target=\"_blank\">NCWIT Aspirations in Computing Award</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://codenow.org/apply/\" target=\"_blank\">CodeNow.org</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','article',0,30,30,'und',0,'<p>We’d like to invite you to find out what it’s like to help shape the minds of tomorrow by giving you the opportunity to volunteer at our next event. If you are passionate about coding and teaching children, join us. Everyone is welcome, regardless of technical ability. To learn more about mentoring, watch brief promo video:</p>\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/HntLmTymmyc\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" width=\"560\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are unable to attend meetings and mentor at&nbsp;CoderDojo NOVA, but would still like to help, we are in need of volunteers and sponsors who can simply help spread the word, recruit new mentors, donate equipment, space and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All teaching sessions run between 1 pm&nbsp;and 3 pm with breaks and food provided.</li>\r\n	<li>Volunteers are requested to be there between 12:30 pm and 3 pm on the event day (Sunday) for setup and breakdown.</li>\r\n	<li>The only thing you need to bring is yourself, willingness to help new programmers learn, and a fun, cheerful attitude!</li>\r\n	<li>If you want to volunteer, please email us at coderdojonova@gmail.com.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','article',0,31,31,'und',0,'<div>\r\n<h3>PARENTS</h3>\r\n\r\n<h2>Does my child need to already know code?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are no requirements for attending a CoderDojo class other than bringing yourself and a desire to learn. Every Dojo teaches a basic introduction to making a webpage as a starting point to learning how to code. From there, children begin to learn how to code in more advanced languages by learning from each other and from the mentors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the age range of the students?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Approximately 7–17 years old.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>On average how many students are at each session?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Between 20–40&nbsp;students.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What level IT skills do students need at the start?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It’s recommended that they have used a computer and browsed the internet before but no real computer skills are needed. The point is to introduce kids to programming and inspire them to explore technology on their own.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What level of code you are offering at classes?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Our CoderDojo develops content to suit the students and mentors in attendance. CoderDojo recommends HTML as a good starting point to demonstrate to kids that they can actually create content. This will encourage progression into more complex programming with functions/loops/variables etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who are the volunteers?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Volunteers include parents, teachers and programmers from the industry who are enthusiastic about helping kids to develop their coding skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Can I stay with my child during the class?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes! We highly encourage parents to stay with their children throughout the process. This allows everyone to learn something new and amazing!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do we need to provide a laptop?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Parents are supposed to bring their own laptop to our Dojo. &nbsp;However, for those who can not afford it we can provide a loaner. &nbsp;We have also partnered with <a href=\"http://codestarter.org\">Codestarter </a>to give away free laptops to kids whose parents can not afford to buy one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>MENTORS</h3>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do I need to have programming knowledge to be a mentor?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>No. All a mentor needs are problem solving skills, the ability to google, and a passion for technology.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Will I be expected to teach at sessions?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>No, kids will be directed to websites to learn from. Mentors will provide assistance, problem solving, and encourage collaboration between kids.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do I need to bring anything?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>No. Each child will have their own laptop.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do I have to attend every session to be a mentor?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You’re not required to attend every session, though we’d love to have you!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>I have kids interested in coding, can I bring them along?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course! Let us know if you want them to be in your group and we’ll make arrangements.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>I have kids interested in coding, can I bring them along?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course! Let us know if you want them to be in your group and we’ll make arrangements.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','article',0,32,32,'und',0,'<p>The ‘Hour of Code’ is nationwide initiative by Computer Science Education Week [csedweek.org] and Code.org to introduce millions of students to one hour of computer science and computer programming. &nbsp;Computer Science Education Week is an annual celebration in recognition of the birthday of computing pioneer Admiral Grace Hopper (December 9, 1906).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In partnership with Google, SySTEMic Solutions, Neustar, Agilex, and Transit Labs, CoderDojo NOVA is challenging Northern Virginia&nbsp;youth to participate in the Hour of Code. That means just one hour of learning the basics of computer science. For partnership inquiries, please contact us at coderdojonova@gmail.com.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sunday, December 7, 12 – 2 p.m.</strong><br />\r\n(CoderDojo NOVA kids)<br />\r\n<strong><em>NOVA Medical Campus&nbsp;– Room 254/256</em></strong><br />\r\n6699 Springfield Center Drive, Springfield, VA 22150<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Monday, December 8</strong><br />\r\n(Area Middle and High School Students)<br />\r\n<strong><em>Agilex&nbsp;</em></strong><br />\r\n5155 Parkstone Dr, Chantilly, VA 20151</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Wednesday, December 10</strong><br />\r\n(Area Middle and High School Students)<br />\r\n<strong><em>Neustar</em></strong><br />\r\n1861 International Drive 6th Floor McLean, VA 22102</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Thursday, December 11</strong><br />\r\n(Area Middle and High School Students)<br />\r\n<strong><em>Google</em></strong><br />\r\n1818 Library St #400, Reston, VA 20190<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Friday, December 12</strong><br />\r\n(Area Middle and High School Students)<br />\r\n<strong><em>Google</em></strong><br />\r\n1818 Library St #400, Reston, VA 20190</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sunday, December 14</strong><br />\r\n(CoderDojo NOVA and DC kids)<br />\r\n<strong><em>Transit Labs @1776</em></strong><br />\r\n1133 15th Street, NW, Washington, D.C. 20005</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The above events are made possible by the generous support of the following organizations:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>About Google</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Google-Logo.png\"><img alt=\"Google-Logo\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-312\" src=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Google-Logo.png\" style=\"height:120px; width:310px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google&nbsp;is a global technology leader focused on improving the ways people connect with information. Google’s innovations in web search and advertising have made its website a top Internet property and its brand one of the most recognized in the world. &nbsp;More information is available at <a href=\"http://www.google.com/about/company/\">http://www.google.com/about/company/</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About NOVA’s SySTEMic Solutions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/SySTEMic-logo-244x220.jpg\"><img alt=\"SySTEMic-logo-244x220\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-311\" src=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/SySTEMic-logo-244x220.jpg\" style=\"height:216px; width:239px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>SySTEMic Solutions is a program of the Northern Virginia Community College (NOVA) that provides a pathway to employment or higher education with a degree in a STEM-related field.&nbsp;The program partners with the three local school divisions, counties, and private industries, to encourage more students to consider STEM careers. &nbsp;More information is available at <a href=\"http://www.nvcc.edu/systemic/index.html\">http://www.nvcc.edu/systemic/index.html</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About Neustar</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Neustar-Inc-logo.png\"><img alt=\"Neustar-Inc-logo\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-313\" src=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Neustar-Inc-logo.png\" style=\"height:69px; width:275px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neustar, Inc.&nbsp;(NYSE:NSR) is the first real-time provider of cloud-based information services and data analytics, enabling marketing and IT security professionals to promote and protect their businesses. With a commitment to privacy and neutrality,&nbsp;Neustar&nbsp;operates complex data registries and uses its expertise to deliver actionable, data-driven insights that help clients make high-value business decisions in real time, one customer interaction at a time. More information is available at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.neustar.biz&amp;esheet=50935533&amp;newsitemid=20140904005051&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=www.neustar.biz&amp;index=3&amp;md5=38ca37bf83d8176d6e469241b17046c5\">www.neustar.biz</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About Agilex</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/agilexlogo-1.png\"><img alt=\"agilexlogo (1)\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-314\" src=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/agilexlogo-1.png\" style=\"height:83px; width:275px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Agilex is an award-winning, employee-owned provider of mission and technology solutions to the national security, healthcare and public sectors. Headquartered in Chantilly, Virginia, we serve a majority of the Cabinet-level federal departments, including the Departments of Defense, Health &amp; Human Services, Homeland Security, Justice and Veterans Affairs; members of the Intelligence Community; and a number of independent and quasi-independent agencies, such as Amtrak and the United States Postal Service. By bringing together Agility with Expertise, our 600 professionals help clients&nbsp;<em>Realize the Value of Information®. &nbsp;</em>More information is available at <a href=\"http://www.agilex.com\">www.agilex.com</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About Transit Labs</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/transitlabs.jpg\"><img alt=\"transitlabs\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-315\" src=\"http://www.coderdojonova.co/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/transitlabs.jpg\" style=\"height:61px; width:301px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transit Labs is a data analytics company dedicated to building smarter cities by improving data collection, reporting, analysis and modeling practices and harnessing the power of big data to better inform transit decision-making. &nbsp;It works with transit systems, states and regions, and federal analysts to create a better public transportation system. &nbsp;More information is available at<a href=\"http://www.transitlabs.com/\"> www.transitlabs.com</a>.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html');
